Global Moran’s I was applied to detect spatial autocorrelation for the durations of emerging snail-infected sites among the three categories (marshlands, inner embankments and hills). A row standardization (a technique for adjusting the weights in a spatial weight matrix) was conducted. The method of inverse distance was applied to determine the spatial relationship. The value of the Moran's I ranges between −1 (maximum negative association) and 1 (maximum positive association), with a zero value indicating a random spatial pattern [23]. A Z-score > 1.96 or < \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
